The paper focuses on the comparison of multimedia processing and machine learning methods for automatic audiovisual health and emotion analysis, which falls under the scope of multimedia (cs.MM) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also mentions the use of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques for affect recognition. Finally, the paper discusses the performance of baseline systems, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG).
